frameDefinitions: The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
A Cause, animate or inanimate, causes a process, the Effect, to begin.
An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.
An Agent finishes an Activity, which can no longer logically continue.

This frame is concerned with the idea that people (Participant_1, Participant_2, or Participants) participate in an organized, rule-governed activity (the Competition) in order to achieve some advantageous outcome (often the Prize).
A Cause leads to the formation of a Created_entity.
frameExamples: The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
The murder of Sergei Kirov <t>set off</t> a chain of events that culminated in the Great Terror of the 1930s.
After discovering her knack for organization, she decided to try to  <t>launch</t> a career in human resources.
Jason <t>completed</t> grading the papers late Sunday night.

An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces an effect. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.

This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Process</fen> is initiated.

This role identifies the first (or only) participant in a competition.

The period of time when the <fen>Competition</fen> occurs.

Where the event takes place.
